ent elementor-element-d6f2b14\" data-id=\"d6f2b14\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-0f6684c elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"0f6684c\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9be6ef6\" data-id=\"9be6ef6\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-62d675e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"62d675e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Importance of Controlling Raccoon Populations<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ce09106 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ce09106\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Raccoons are notorious for their scavenging habits and are commonly found in urban areas rummaging through trash cans, gardens, and pet food dishes. While they may seem harmless at first glance, raccoons can cause significant damage to property and pose a threat to human health. They carry diseases such as rabies, leptospirosis, salmonella, and roundworms that can easily spread to humans and other animals.<\/p><p>Controlling the raccoon population is essential for maintaining a safe environment. One way of doing this is by preventing them from accessing food sources such as garbage cans and bird feeders. Homeowners should secure their trash cans with tight-fitting lids or store them in an enclosed area. They should also avoid leaving pet food outside overnight.<\/p><p>Another method of controlling raccoon populations is by trapping them humanely. It&#8217;s crucial to note that trapping raccoons without a permit is illegal in most parts of the country. Therefore, it&#8217;s best to contact a ACME Pest Solutions that will trap the animals safely and release them into the wild, away from residential areas. By taking these measures, homeowners can prevent property damage caused by raccoons while ensuring public safety from related health risks.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Raccoon Identification Color Size Description Color Most commonly, raccoons have grayish-brown fur with black highlights around their face and tail. Size Raccoons measure about 2-3 feet long from the nose to the tip of the tail. Description Raccoons are known for their characteristic black mask around their eyes and striped tail. They have a stocky &#8230; <a title=\"Raccoons\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/raccoons\/\" aria-label=\"More on Raccoons\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6649,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[12],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6487","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-raccoon-control"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6487"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.c